{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":849,"text":"First, a video."},{"time":9397,"text":"Yes, it is a scrambled egg."},{"time":14151,"text":"But as you look at it,"},{"time":15508,"text":"I hope you'll begin to feel\njust slightly uneasy."},{"time":21389,"text":"Because you may notice\nthat what's actually happening"},{"time":24751,"text":"is that the egg is unscrambling itself."},{"time":27000,"text":"And you'll now see the yolk\nand the white have separated."},{"time":29723,"text":"And now they're going to be\npoured back into the egg."},{"time":32770,"text":"And we all know in our heart of hearts"},{"time":35262,"text":"that this is not the way\nthe universe works."},{"time":39436,"text":"A scrambled egg is mush --\ntasty mush -- but it's mush."},{"time":42565,"text":"An egg is a beautiful, sophisticated thing"},{"time":45000,"text":"that can create even more\nsophisticated things,"},{"time":47263,"text":"such as chickens."},{"time":49072,"text":"And we know in our heart of hearts"},{"time":51000,"text":"that the universe does not travel\nfrom mush to complexity."},{"time":55190,"text":"In fact, this gut instinct"},{"time":57609,"text":"is reflected in one of the most\nfundamental laws of physics,"},{"time":60505,"text":"the second law of thermodynamics,\nor the law of entropy."},{"time":63902,"text":"What that says basically"},{"time":65685,"text":"is that the general\ntendency of the universe"},{"time":68836,"text":"is to move from order and structure"},{"time":72463,"text":"to lack of order, lack of structure --"},{"time":75151,"text":"in fact, to mush."},{"time":76639,"text":"And that's why that video\nfeels a bit strange."}]},{"cues":[{"time":80425,"text":"And yet, look around us."},{"time":84194,"text":"What we see around us\nis staggering complexity."},{"time":88289,"text":"Eric Beinhocker estimates\nthat in New York City alone,"},{"time":91602,"text":"there are some 10 billion SKUs,\nor distinct commodities, being traded."},{"time":95672,"text":"That's hundreds of times\nas many species as there are on Earth."},{"time":100000,"text":"And they're being traded by a species\nof almost seven billion individuals,"},{"time":104000,"text":"who are linked by trade,\ntravel, and the Internet"},{"time":107409,"text":"into a global system\nof stupendous complexity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":112566,"text":"So here's a great puzzle:"},{"time":114931,"text":"in a universe ruled\nby the second law of thermodynamics,"},{"time":119602,"text":"how is it possible"},{"time":121430,"text":"to generate the sort\nof complexity I've described,"},{"time":124000,"text":"the sort of complexity\nrepresented by you and me"},{"time":127812,"text":"and the convention center?"},{"time":130859,"text":"Well, the answer seems to be,"},{"time":132836,"text":"the universe can create complexity,"},{"time":136000,"text":"but with great difficulty."},{"time":138610,"text":"In pockets,"},{"time":139731,"text":"there appear\nwhat my colleague, Fred Spier,"},{"time":142072,"text":"calls \"Goldilocks conditions\" --"},{"time":144238,"text":"not too hot, not too cold,"},{"time":146313,"text":"just right for the creation of complexity."},{"time":149000,"text":"And slightly more complex things appear."},{"time":151291,"text":"And where you have\nslightly more complex things,"},{"time":153554,"text":"you can get slightly more complex things."},{"time":155950,"text":"And in this way, complexity\nbuilds stage by stage."},{"time":160875,"text":"Each stage is magical"},{"time":163177,"text":"because it creates the impression\nof something utterly new"},{"time":166774,"text":"appearing almost out of nowhere\nin the universe."},{"time":169601,"text":"We refer in big history to these moments\nas threshold moments."},{"time":173871,"text":"And at each threshold,\nthe going gets tougher."},{"time":177000,"text":"The complex things get more fragile,"},{"time":180266,"text":"more vulnerable;"},{"time":182000,"text":"the Goldilocks conditions\nget more stringent,"},{"time":185555,"text":"and it's more difficult\nto create complexity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":189468,"text":"Now, we, as extremely complex creatures,"},{"time":192796,"text":"desperately need to know this story"},{"time":195000,"text":"of how the universe creates complexity\ndespite the second law,"},{"time":199682,"text":"and why complexity means\nvulnerability and fragility."},{"time":205485,"text":"And that's the story\nthat we tell in big history."},{"time":208429,"text":"But to do it, you have do something"},{"time":210160,"text":"that may, at first sight,\nseem completely impossible."},{"time":212889,"text":"You have to survey the whole\nhistory of the universe."},{"time":217488,"text":"So let's do it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":219000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":220933,"text":"Let's begin by winding the timeline back"},{"time":224403,"text":"13.7 billion years,"},{"time":227323,"text":"to the beginning of time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":237321,"text":"Around us, there's nothing."},{"time":239726,"text":"There's not even time or space."},{"time":243214,"text":"Imagine the darkest,\nemptiest thing you can"},{"time":246936,"text":"and cube it a gazillion times\nand that's where we are."},{"time":250732,"text":"And then suddenly,"},{"time":253096,"text":"bang!"},{"time":254128,"text":"A universe appears, an entire universe."},{"time":256359,"text":"And we've crossed our first threshold."},{"time":258239,"text":"The universe is tiny;\nit's smaller than an atom."},{"time":260636,"text":"It's incredibly hot."},{"time":262000,"text":"It contains everything\nthat's in today's universe,"},{"time":264549,"text":"so you can imagine, it's busting."},{"time":266367,"text":"And it's expanding at incredible speed."},{"time":269000,"text":"And at first, it's just a blur,"},{"time":270937,"text":"but very quickly distinct things\nbegin to appear in that blur."},{"time":274483,"text":"Within the first second,"},{"time":276000,"text":"energy itself shatters\ninto distinct forces"},{"time":279000,"text":"including electromagnetism and gravity."},{"time":282106,"text":"And energy does something\nelse quite magical:"},{"time":284558,"text":"it congeals to form matter --"},{"time":287814,"text":"quarks that will create protons"},{"time":290168,"text":"and leptons that include electrons."},{"time":292330,"text":"And all of that happens\nin the first second."}]},{"cues":[{"time":294457,"text":"Now we move forward 380,000 years."},{"time":299000,"text":"That's twice as long as humans\nhave been on this planet."},{"time":302671,"text":"And now simple atoms appear\nof hydrogen and helium."},{"time":308617,"text":"Now I want to pause for a moment,"},{"time":310244,"text":"380,000 years after the origins\nof the universe,"},{"time":313000,"text":"because we actually know quite a lot\nabout the universe at this stage."},{"time":317513,"text":"We know above all\nthat it was extremely simple."},{"time":320458,"text":"It consisted of huge clouds\nof hydrogen and helium atoms,"},{"time":324281,"text":"and they have no structure."},{"time":326233,"text":"They're really a sort of cosmic mush."},{"time":329392,"text":"But that's not completely true."},{"time":331472,"text":"Recent studies"},{"time":333000,"text":"by satellites such as the WMAP satellite"},{"time":335885,"text":"have shown that, in fact,"},{"time":337486,"text":"there are just tiny differences\nin that background."},{"time":340259,"text":"What you see here,"},{"time":342000,"text":"the blue areas are about a thousandth\nof a degree cooler"},{"time":346330,"text":"than the red areas."},{"time":347746,"text":"These are tiny differences,"},{"time":349143,"text":"but it was enough\nfor the universe to move on"},{"time":351437,"text":"to the next stage of building complexity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":353436,"text":"And this is how it works."},{"time":355635,"text":"Gravity is more powerful\nwhere there's more stuff."},{"time":360557,"text":"So where you get slightly denser areas,"},{"time":362899,"text":"gravity starts compacting clouds\nof hydrogen and helium atoms."},{"time":366840,"text":"So we can imagine the early universe\nbreaking up into a billion clouds."},{"time":370414,"text":"And each cloud is compacted,"},{"time":372240,"text":"gravity gets more powerful\nas density increases,"},{"time":375280,"text":"the temperature begins to rise\nat the center of each cloud,"},{"time":378398,"text":"and then, at the center,"},{"time":379711,"text":"the temperature crosses\nthe threshold temperature"},{"time":382573,"text":"of 10 million degrees,"},{"time":384163,"text":"protons start to fuse,"},{"time":386592,"text":"there's a huge release of energy,"},{"time":389000,"text":"and --"},{"time":390457,"text":"bam!"},{"time":391497,"text":"We have our first stars."},{"time":393678,"text":"From about 200 million years\nafter the Big Bang,"},{"time":397560,"text":"stars begin to appear\nall through the universe,"},{"time":400991,"text":"billions of them."},{"time":402499,"text":"And the universe is now\nsignificantly more interesting"},{"time":405379,"text":"and more complex."}]},{"cues":[{"time":407928,"text":"Stars will create\nthe Goldilocks conditions"},{"time":411068,"text":"for crossing two new thresholds."},{"time":413371,"text":"When very large stars die,"},{"time":415974,"text":"they create temperatures so high"},{"time":418319,"text":"that protons begin to fuse\nin all sorts of exotic combinations,"},{"time":421976,"text":"to form all the elements\nof the periodic table."},{"time":424830,"text":"If, like me, you're wearing a gold ring,"},{"time":427150,"text":"it was forged in a supernova explosion."},{"time":430618,"text":"So now the universe\nis chemically more complex."},{"time":433841,"text":"And in a chemically more complex universe,"},{"time":436230,"text":"it's possible to make more things."},{"time":438698,"text":"And what starts happening\nis that, around young suns,"},{"time":442214,"text":"young stars,"},{"time":444000,"text":"all these elements combine,\nthey swirl around,"},{"time":446215,"text":"the energy of the star stirs them around,"},{"time":449019,"text":"they form particles, they form snowflakes,\nthey form little dust motes,"},{"time":453768,"text":"they form rocks, they form asteroids,"},{"time":455988,"text":"and eventually,\nthey form planets and moons."},{"time":458607,"text":"And that is how our\nsolar system was formed,"},{"time":461581,"text":"four and a half billion years ago."},{"time":465193,"text":"Rocky planets like our Earth\nare significantly more complex than stars"},{"time":470590,"text":"because they contain\na much greater diversity of materials."},{"time":473376,"text":"So we've crossed a fourth\nthreshold of complexity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":477671,"text":"Now, the going gets tougher."},{"time":481151,"text":"The next stage introduces entities\nthat are significantly more fragile,"},{"time":485453,"text":"significantly more vulnerable,"},{"time":487389,"text":"but they're also much more creative"},{"time":490000,"text":"and much more capable\nof generating further complexity."},{"time":493346,"text":"I'm talking, of course,\nabout living organisms."},{"time":497474,"text":"Living organisms are created by chemistry."},{"time":499641,"text":"We are huge packages of chemicals."},{"time":502855,"text":"So, chemistry is dominated\nby the electromagnetic force."},{"time":506000,"text":"That operates over smaller\nscales than gravity,"},{"time":508263,"text":"which explains why you and I\nare smaller than stars or planets."},{"time":512773,"text":"Now, what are the ideal\nconditions for chemistry?"},{"time":515614,"text":"What are the Goldilocks conditions?"},{"time":517408,"text":"Well, first, you need energy,"},{"time":519789,"text":"but not too much."},{"time":521405,"text":"In the center of a star,\nthere's so much energy"},{"time":523684,"text":"that any atoms that combine\nwill just get busted apart again."},{"time":526850,"text":"But not too little."},{"time":528382,"text":"In intergalactic space,"},{"time":529637,"text":"there's so little energy\nthat atoms can't combine."},{"time":533118,"text":"What you want is just the right amount,"},{"time":535000,"text":"and planets, it turns out, are just right,"},{"time":537024,"text":"because they're close to stars,\nbut not too close."}]},{"cues":[{"time":540134,"text":"You also need a great diversity\nof chemical elements,"},{"time":543753,"text":"and you need liquids, such as water."},{"time":546785,"text":"Why?"},{"time":547856,"text":"Well, in gases, atoms move\npast each other so fast"},{"time":551752,"text":"that they can't hitch up."},{"time":553690,"text":"In solids,"},{"time":555436,"text":"atoms are stuck together, they can't move."},{"time":558000,"text":"In liquids,"},{"time":559742,"text":"they can cruise and cuddle"},{"time":562804,"text":"and link up to form molecules."},{"time":565780,"text":"Now, where do you find\nsuch Goldilocks conditions?"},{"time":568674,"text":"Well, planets are great,"},{"time":570690,"text":"and our early Earth was almost perfect."},{"time":574777,"text":"It was just the right\ndistance from its star"},{"time":576849,"text":"to contain huge oceans of liquid water."},{"time":579000,"text":"And deep beneath those oceans,"},{"time":581000,"text":"at cracks in the Earth's crust,"},{"time":583000,"text":"you've got heat seeping up\nfrom inside the Earth,"},{"time":586000,"text":"and you've got a great\ndiversity of elements."},{"time":588151,"text":"So at those deep oceanic vents,"},{"time":590721,"text":"fantastic chemistry began to happen,"},{"time":593000,"text":"and atoms combined in all sorts\nof exotic combinations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":597000,"text":"But of course, life is more\nthan just exotic chemistry."},{"time":601794,"text":"How do you stabilize those huge molecules"},{"time":605575,"text":"that seem to be viable?"},{"time":607690,"text":"Well, it's here that life introduces\nan entirely new trick."},{"time":612960,"text":"You don't stabilize the individual;"},{"time":615519,"text":"you stabilize the template,"},{"time":617646,"text":"the thing that carries information,"},{"time":619775,"text":"and you allow the template to copy itself."},{"time":622016,"text":"And DNA, of course,\nis the beautiful molecule"},{"time":625191,"text":"that contains that information."},{"time":627541,"text":"You'll be familiar\nwith the double helix of DNA."},{"time":630380,"text":"Each rung contains information."},{"time":632920,"text":"So, DNA contains information\nabout how to make living organisms."},{"time":638055,"text":"And DNA also copies itself."},{"time":640003,"text":"So, it copies itself"},{"time":641233,"text":"and scatters the templates\nthrough the ocean."},{"time":643939,"text":"So the information spreads."},{"time":645757,"text":"Notice that information\nhas become part of our story."},{"time":648877,"text":"The real beauty of DNA though\nis in its imperfections."},{"time":652546,"text":"As it copies itself,\nonce in every billion rungs,"},{"time":656498,"text":"there tends to be an error."},{"time":658267,"text":"And what that means\nis that DNA is, in effect, learning."},{"time":663000,"text":"It's accumulating new ways\nof making living organisms"},{"time":666344,"text":"because some of those errors work."},{"time":667988,"text":"So DNA's learning"},{"time":669210,"text":"and it's building greater\ndiversity and greater complexity."},{"time":672468,"text":"And we can see this happening\nover the last four billion years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":675674,"text":"For most of that time of life on Earth,"},{"time":677873,"text":"living organisms have been\nrelatively simple --"},{"time":680134,"text":"single cells."},{"time":681546,"text":"But they had great diversity,\nand, inside, great complexity."},{"time":685411,"text":"Then from about 600\nto 800 million years ago,"},{"time":688339,"text":"multi-celled organisms appear."},{"time":690454,"text":"You get fungi, you get fish,"},{"time":692979,"text":"you get plants,"},{"time":694518,"text":"you get amphibia, you get reptiles,"},{"time":697253,"text":"and then, of course,\nyou get the dinosaurs."},{"time":700739,"text":"And occasionally, there are disasters."},{"time":704326,"text":"Sixty-five million years ago,"},{"time":706739,"text":"an asteroid landed on Earth"},{"time":708727,"text":"near the Yucatan Peninsula,"},{"time":710541,"text":"creating conditions equivalent\nto those of a nuclear war,"},{"time":713533,"text":"and the dinosaurs were wiped out."},{"time":715906,"text":"Terrible news for the dinosaurs,"},{"time":719000,"text":"but great news\nfor our mammalian ancestors,"},{"time":722779,"text":"who flourished"},{"time":724000,"text":"in the niches left empty by the dinosaurs."},{"time":727681,"text":"And we human beings are part\nof that creative evolutionary pulse"},{"time":732760,"text":"that began 65 million years ago"},{"time":735120,"text":"with the landing of an asteroid."}]},{"cues":[{"time":738536,"text":"Humans appeared about 200,000 years ago."},{"time":741274,"text":"And I believe we count\nas a threshold in this great story."},{"time":745646,"text":"Let me explain why."},{"time":747440,"text":"We've seen that DNA learns in a sense,"},{"time":750495,"text":"it accumulates information."},{"time":752306,"text":"But it is so slow."},{"time":754868,"text":"DNA accumulates information\nthrough random errors,"},{"time":758364,"text":"some of which just happen to work."},{"time":761230,"text":"But DNA had actually generated\na faster way of learning:"},{"time":763888,"text":"it had produced organisms with brains,"},{"time":766690,"text":"and those organisms\ncan learn in real time."},{"time":769933,"text":"They accumulate information, they learn."},{"time":772283,"text":"The sad thing is, when they die,"},{"time":775132,"text":"the information dies with them."},{"time":777219,"text":"Now what makes humans different\nis human language."},{"time":781230,"text":"We are blessed with a language,\na system of communication,"},{"time":784017,"text":"so powerful and so precise"},{"time":786662,"text":"that we can share what we've learned\nwith such precision"},{"time":789844,"text":"that it can accumulate\nin the collective memory."},{"time":792757,"text":"And that means"},{"time":794000,"text":"it can outlast the individuals\nwho learned that information,"},{"time":797803,"text":"and it can accumulate\nfrom generation to generation."},{"time":801000,"text":"And that's why, as a species,\nwe're so creative and so powerful,"},{"time":805080,"text":"and that's why we have a history."},{"time":807755,"text":"We seem to be the only species\nin four billion years"},{"time":811080,"text":"to have this gift."}]},{"cues":[{"time":812797,"text":"I call this ability collective learning."},{"time":816735,"text":"It's what makes us different."},{"time":818426,"text":"We can see it at work\nin the earliest stages of human history."},{"time":822689,"text":"We evolved as a species\nin the savanna lands of Africa,"},{"time":826000,"text":"but then you see humans migrating\ninto new environments,"},{"time":829484,"text":"into desert lands, into jungles,"},{"time":831658,"text":"into the Ice Age tundra of Siberia --"},{"time":834118,"text":"tough, tough environment --"},{"time":835587,"text":"into the Americas, into Australasia."},{"time":837944,"text":"Each migration involved learning --"},{"time":840005,"text":"learning new ways of exploiting\nthe environment,"},{"time":842512,"text":"new ways of dealing\nwith their surroundings."}]},{"cues":[{"time":844710,"text":"Then 10,000 years ago,"},{"time":846550,"text":"exploiting a sudden\nchange in global climate"},{"time":849569,"text":"with the end of the last ice age,"},{"time":851165,"text":"humans learned to farm."},{"time":853363,"text":"Farming was an energy bonanza."},{"time":855823,"text":"And exploiting that energy,\nhuman populations multiplied."},{"time":859674,"text":"Human societies got larger,\ndenser, more interconnected."},{"time":863841,"text":"And then from about 500 years ago,"},{"time":867216,"text":"humans began to link up globally"},{"time":869279,"text":"through shipping, through trains,"},{"time":871684,"text":"through telegraph, through the Internet,"},{"time":874000,"text":"until now we seem to form\na single global brain"},{"time":879215,"text":"of almost seven billion individuals."},{"time":881371,"text":"And that brain is learning at warp speed."},{"time":885312,"text":"And in the last 200 years,\nsomething else has happened."},{"time":887908,"text":"We've stumbled on another energy bonanza"},{"time":890598,"text":"in fossil fuels."},{"time":891749,"text":"So fossil fuels and collective\nlearning together"},{"time":894476,"text":"explain the staggering complexity\nwe see around us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":901245,"text":"So --"},{"time":903408,"text":"Here we are,"},{"time":904749,"text":"back at the convention center."},{"time":906297,"text":"We've been on a journey,\na return journey, of 13.7 billion years."},{"time":911707,"text":"I hope you agree this is a powerful story."},{"time":914200,"text":"And it's a story in which humans\nplay an astonishing and creative role."},{"time":919206,"text":"But it also contains warnings."},{"time":922214,"text":"Collective learning is a very,\nvery powerful force,"},{"time":926571,"text":"and it's not clear\nthat we humans are in charge of it."},{"time":931863,"text":"I remember very vividly\nas a child growing up in England,"},{"time":934956,"text":"living through the Cuban Missile Crisis."},{"time":937587,"text":"For a few days, the entire biosphere"},{"time":941222,"text":"seemed to be on the verge of destruction."},{"time":944214,"text":"And the same weapons are still here,"},{"time":947403,"text":"and they are still armed."},{"time":949744,"text":"If we avoid that trap,\nothers are waiting for us."},{"time":953387,"text":"We're burning fossil fuels at such a rate"},{"time":956000,"text":"that we seem to be undermining\nthe Goldilocks conditions"},{"time":959435,"text":"that made it possible\nfor human civilizations"},{"time":961687,"text":"to flourish over the last 10,000 years."},{"time":965373,"text":"So what big history can do"},{"time":967673,"text":"is show us the nature\nof our complexity and fragility"},{"time":971018,"text":"and the dangers that face us,"},{"time":972966,"text":"but it can also show us\nour power with collective learning."}]},{"cues":[{"time":977326,"text":"And now, finally --"},{"time":980397,"text":"this is what I want."},{"time":984188,"text":"I want my grandson, Daniel,"},{"time":987244,"text":"and his friends and his generation,"},{"time":990025,"text":"throughout the world,"},{"time":991842,"text":"to know the story of big history,"},{"time":994706,"text":"and to know it so well"},{"time":996769,"text":"that they understand\nboth the challenges that face us"},{"time":1000459,"text":"and the opportunities that face us."},{"time":1003000,"text":"And that's why a group of us"},{"time":1004904,"text":"are building a free, online syllabus"},{"time":1007940,"text":"in big history"},{"time":1009282,"text":"for high-school students\nthroughout the world."},{"time":1011965,"text":"We believe that big history"},{"time":1014425,"text":"will be a vital\nintellectual tool for them,"},{"time":1017000,"text":"as Daniel and his generation"},{"time":1019867,"text":"face the huge challenges"},{"time":1022239,"text":"and also the huge opportunities"},{"time":1024318,"text":"ahead of them at this threshold moment"},{"time":1027797,"text":"in the history of our beautiful planet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1031733,"text":"I thank you for your attention."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1033305,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}